title: Infinite Spokes
description: An interactive map of Cambridge and Boston showcasing bike activity and bike routes. The visualization shows cycling patterns, helping users explore urban bike traffic and infrastructure in real time.

title: Mouse Estrous Cycle Visualization
description: This interactive tool explores temperature and activity patterns across the four phases of the female mouse estrous cycle: Proestrus, Estrus, Metestrus, and Diestrus. It lets you observe daily changes, compare phases, and uncover relationships between physiological patterns..

title: ESG Stock Predictor
description: This project investigated the integration of Environmental, Social, and Governance criteria with historical financial data to improve stock return predictions and promote sustainable investing.

title: Recipe Analysis
description: This analysis is aimed at understanding whether recipes with higher calorie counts are rated differently than those with lower calorie counts. I leveraged predictive models to forecast average ratings based on recipe attributes and reported our findings.

title: Knowledge Graph
description: This project extracts and visualizes relationships from clinical research papers using OpenAI GPT-4 and PyVis for creating interactive knowledge graphs. The tool is designed for tele-mental health providers to make informed decisions about treatments for anxiety and depression based on clinical research.
